INSERT INTO `qe_product` VALUES ('2', '2', 'Bubble Ball Solar String Lights 30 LED 8 Modes Blue', '<span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Product Features</span><span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1.Solar-powered decorative string lights, with no extra electricity consumption incurred.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">2.Waterproof, suitable for indoor and outdoor.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">3.If one light goes out, the rest will stay lit up.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">4.Powered by solar light with efficient solar panel kit, energy-saving and eco-friendly.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">NOTE:</span><span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;The solar panel should be directly facing sunlight to be recharged.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Specification</span><span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1.Brand: Qedertek&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">2.Color: Blue&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">3.Material: Plastic&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">4.Diameter of bulb: 1 inch&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">5.Number of lights: 30 LED&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">6.Switch: ON/OFF, MODE&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">7.Solar panel: 2V 100mA&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">8.Rechargeable Ni-MH battery: 600mAh&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">9.Charging time: 6 hours&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">10.Working time: 8 hours&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">11.Total length: 20ft&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">12.Length from solar panel to first light: 5ft&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">What\'s in the Box?</span><span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1 x Qedertek 30 Bubble Globes Lights&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1 x Ground Stick&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1 x Solar Panel&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1 x Instruction&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">How the solar panel works?</span><span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1. During the daytime, solar panel converses solar energyand converts it to electrical energy stored in the rechargable battery.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">2. The battery release the energy as light power when it\'s dark.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">3. There is a Ni-MH AA rechargeable battery in solar box, which is durable, and can be easily changed out.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">4. When you find its lighting hours are getting shorter or dimming, it is recommended that you replace the battery.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Buy with confidence. We have professional after-sale customer service. If there any issue with it, please contact us, and we will response and solve it within 24 hours (replace or refund). Your satisfaction is our top priority.</span>', '<ul class=\"a-unordered-list a-vertical a-spacing-none\" style=\"color:#949494;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">SOLAR POWERED - These LED lights decorate your garden with energy from the solar and do not require additional cost.</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">EASY TO USE - The solar panel is easily installed. These lights are automaticall on and off according to surrounding brightness. Controlling buttons for power and modes are on the back of panel box. The mode switch allows you to choose your favorite lighting modes, which makes your space more of your persoanlity</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">LONG-WORKING TIME - 600mAh rechargeable battery can work continuously for 8 hours once fully charged. Just replace the RECHARGEABLE BATTERY WITH NORMAL BATTERY when there is not enough sunshine, then it will work.</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">FASINATING DECORATION and NOVELTY GIFT- with its multicolor bubble crystal bulbs lighting under 8 modes to create dreamily romantic and fairy illumination effects and make the environment stand out. It can be used as GIFT to your FRIENDS or FAMILIES.</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', '<div id=\"question-Tx3M0052AQW39P6\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n			<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n			What kind of batteries do these take?\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n			<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n			<span>They are solar powered</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By samantha on December 9, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx3M0052AQW39P6\"> \r\n			<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx3M0052AQW39P6-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n				<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n					<span>Batteries are included. The box appears to be AA size however I did not try to open the battery box.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By john813 on December 5, 2016</span> \r\n				</div>\r\n				<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n					<span>I\'m not sure, I have not removed the casing because its solar.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By michelle on December 5, 2016</span> \r\n				</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>', 'Solar String Lights: 30 LED Blue Bubble Ball Festive Lights, Park Lighting Decoration, Crystal Goble Lights and Decor - Qedertek', 'bubble ball string lights,festive lights,bubble ball solar string lights,park lighting,lights and decor', 'Search for bubble ball string lights，you are just right here, 30 LED solar powered, 8 modes, waterproof blue bubble globes lights, widely use for holiday, Christmas garden, patio and party decorating. ', 'https://www.amazon.com/dp/B01IN8GZ0E/', '', '0', '0.00', 'http://images.qedertek.com/59352d70b7f01', '{\"59352d7114d29\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352d7114d29\",\"59352d71293cf\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352d71293cf\",\"59352d7140541\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352d7140541\",\"59352d7154cbe\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352d7154cbe\",\"59352d717ac40\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352d717ac40\"}', '0', '1', '0', '0.00', '1', '1490600442', '1496657265', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `qe_product` VALUES ('3', '7', 'Ultrasonic 100ml Essential Oil Diffusers with Adjustable Mist Mode', '<div id=\"descriptionAndDetails\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-extra-large\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<div id=\"productDescription_feature_div\" class=\"feature\">\r\n		<div id=\"productDescription_feature_div\" class=\"a-row feature\">\r\n			<div id=\"productDescription\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-small\" style=\"margin:0.5em 0px 0em 25px;color:#333333;font-size:small;\">\r\n				<p style=\"margin-left:1em;\">\r\n					<span style=\"font-weight:700;\">Functions:&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n&nbsp;Refresh skin, keep it healthy and moist&nbsp;<br />\r\nHumidify the air&nbsp;<br />\r\nAroma therapy, relieve stress&nbsp;<br />\r\nReduce headaches&nbsp;<br />\r\nContribute to more restful sleep&nbsp;<br />\r\nEase cold and flu symptoms&nbsp;<br />\r\nAlleviate allergies&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:700;\">Specifications:&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n&nbsp;Material: Upper parts PP&nbsp;<br />\r\nCapacity of water tank: About 100ML&nbsp;<br />\r\nInput power: AC 100-240V 50/60HZ&nbsp;<br />\r\nMost advanced ultrasonic technology: 2.4MHZ&nbsp;<br />\r\nWorking time:3 hours in continuous mode, 7 hours in intermittent mode&nbsp;<br />\r\nAutomatic shut off safety system protects the product from being burned out.&nbsp;<br />\r\nCoverage: Aromatherapy 20 square meters, humidification 10 square meters&nbsp;<br />\r\nSize: Diameter 3.94in*Height 5.5in&nbsp;<br />\r\nNet Weight: around 7.05oz&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:700;\">Package includes:&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n&nbsp;1 x Aroma Diffuser&nbsp;<br />\r\n1 x Charger Adaptor&nbsp;<br />\r\n1 x Measuring Cup for Filling Water&nbsp;<br />\r\n1 x User Manual&nbsp;<br />\r\nNote: Oil is not included in this package&nbsp;\r\n				</p>\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"productDetails_feature_div\" class=\"feature\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n</div>', '<ul class=\"a-unordered-list a-vertical a-spacing-none\" style=\"margin-left:18px;color:#949494;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Fill the space with a lovely fragrance and at the same time humidify the air surrounding you. Fragrance can melt away your stress and relieve you from stressful and tiring day, also perfect for masking odors such as the smells of smoking and stale sweat. Mist humidifier can increase moisture in the air to prevent your skin from being dry.</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Super Quiet Ultrasonic Operation- Extremely quiet and pleasant, no noise, heat or vibration, allowing for a deep relaxing sleep. Great for bedrooms, bathrooms, massage rooms, spas, etc. Can be placed on your nightstand, on the desk in the office, etc.</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Shuts Off Automatically if the water runs out, very safe and easy to use, just fill with warm tap water and add a few drops of your favorite essential oil. (Measuring cup is included). No Need for filters or distilled water.</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">LED Light Modes: 7 Mood Lights automatically change from one color to the next, or you can choose one light you like and set it to be steady on. If no need for light, you can turn it off and just let the mist on. Color including: Green, Dark blue, Red, Yellow, Pink, Light blue, White</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Mist Working Modes: Intermittent Mist (30 seconds on/30 seconds off), Continuous Mist, Lights only. Working Time: 3 hours in continuous mist mode, 7 hours in intermittent mist mode. Content: 100ml, Material: PP Hard plastic, BPA Free.</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', '<div id=\"question-Tx1XQWU783CK2NJ\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n			<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n			Can this diffuser be used without the light changing color or be turned off?\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n			<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n			<span>Yes, you can run the diffuser without the light.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amber Todd on March 27, 2017</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx1XQWU783CK2NJ\"> \r\n			<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1XQWU783CK2NJ-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n				<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n					<span>It can be used with or without the light. There is a button for each.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By MissyD on March 27, 2017</span> \r\n				</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx32WSWCWUA854F\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Can this diffuser be used in the living room and get the same affect?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>Dear Neenie, thank you for your question.This diffuser is great for home ï¼living room, bedrooms, bathrooms, etcï¼office, spas, yoga, it can melt away your stress and relieve you from stressful and tiring day, also perfect for masking odors such as the smells of smoking and stale sweat, prevent your skin from being dry.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Qedertek Direct&nbsp;on January 5, 2017</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx3KYV52MUOO0XA\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Do I have to charge this with a computer or can I plug in directly to a wall outlet?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>Plugs into the wall</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By MissyD on January 26, 2017</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx3KYV52MUOO0XA\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx3KYV52MUOO0XA-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>It has a wall adapter AC house current. Needs to be plugged in.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Barry Keippel on January 26, 2017</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>We plug ours into the wall outlet of whichever room we want to infuse. It works beautifully!</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Eleanor B. on January 27, 2017</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-TxW2ZU19LPEAZ2\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Would this be useful just as a humidifier, without the oils?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>Dear Kristin, thank you for your question. This item can be uesd as both humidifier and diffuser, if you don\'t put the oil into the water tenk, it can be used as a cool mist humidifier;and if you put the oil into the water tenk, it can be used as a diffuser.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Qedertek Direct&nbsp;on December 29, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"TxW2ZU19LPEAZ2\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-TxW2ZU19LPEAZ2-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>It does not hold alot of water, but it could be used without the oils to put a little moisture in the air.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By ThriftyTori on December 31, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>', '100ml Ultrasonic Essential Oil Diffusers | Portable Ultrasonic Aromatherapy Diffusers, Features Adjustable Mist Mode，7 Colors, Waterless Auto Shut-off - Qedertek', 'best essential oils humidifiers,advanced aromatherapy essential oil diffusers,100ml ultrasonic essential oil diffusers,portable ultrasonic aromatherapy diffusers', 'If you are looking for best essential oils humidifiers，don\'t miss this 100ml ultrasonic essential oil diffusers，features adjustable mist mode，7 Colors light changing and waterless auto shut-off multi-functions, perfect for bedrooms, bathrooms, massage roo', 'https://www.amazon.com/dp/B01JRTUNJW/', '', '0', '0.00', 'http://images.qedertek.com/59352ce935814', '{\"59352ce97de84\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352ce97de84\",\"59352ce99a162\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352ce99a162\",\"59352ced249d7\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352ced249d7\",\"59352ced36059\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352ced36059\"}', '0', '0', '0', '0.00', '1', '1490949224', '1496657133', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `qe_product` VALUES ('4', '2', 'Solar Powered Blossom Flower String Lights 50 LED Multi-color', '<p>\r\n	<img src=\"https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/aplus-seller-content-images-us-east-1/ATVPDKIKX0DER/A231TAZUOKNIOW/B012VIRJ4I/zrmFYWQrRG2S._UX970_TTW_.jpg\" title=\"Qedertek Blossom Flower Solar String Lights\" alt=\"Qedertek Blossom Flower Solar String Lights\" /> \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Qedertek 50LED Flower Blossom Solar String Lights</span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Products Features&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;1. Solar powered led light strings, no utility energy costs&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;2. Energy saving &amp; eco-friendly LED string lights, high energy conversion rate.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;3. Lighting sensor technology, the string lights will light up automatically at dusk and may automatically turn off at daytime&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Specifications&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\"></span> \r\n</p>\r\n<ul style=\"font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		Light color: Multi-Color (red/yellow/green/purple) &nbsp;\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Solar Panel: 2V/100mA&nbsp;\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Battery type: Rechargeable 600mAH NI-MH Battery&nbsp;\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Switch: ON/OFF, MODE&nbsp;\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Working mode: Flash/Steady on&nbsp;\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Charging time: 6-8hrs&nbsp;\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Light length: 21ft(7m)&nbsp;\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Length between 2 blubs:0.3ft(0.1m)&nbsp;\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Length from Solar panel to first stake: 6.5ft(2m)&nbsp;\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Warm Tips&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;1. If the ground is too hard, try to soften the ground with water before you set up the solar panel&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;2. It is suggested the s</span><span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">olar panel to be fully charged for 8hrs at the first use.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;3. Set up the angle adjustable solar panel where there is enough sunlight&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;4. Turn the light on and set light mode before charging the solar power, so it will light up at dusk.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">What\'s in the box&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;1 x Qedertek 50LED Flower Solar String Lights&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;1 x Solar Panel with Ground Stake&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;1 x User Instruction</span>', '<ul class=\"a-unordered-list a-vertical a-spacing-none\" style=\"color:#949494;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Perfect Holiday Decorative Lights: The solar string lights illuminate during night, add romantic and charming atmosphere to your home, patio, lawn, garden, etc</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Solar Powered String lights: 50 colorful flower blossom LEDs on a 21ft light strand (6.5ft lead cable included), solar panel(2V/100mA) with built-in 600mA NI-MH battery</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Long Working Time: Solar panel convert sunshine into electricity during the day, and it lights up automatically at night for more than 8 hours if solar panel absorbs enough sunlight during day.</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Easy to Operate &amp; Install: Solar panel with garden stakes stand, 2 switches, On/Off and Mode (Steady/Flashing)</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">IP 65 Waterproof: Can withstand all kinds of weather, including heavy rain and snow, perfect for indoor and outdoor decoration</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', '<div id=\"question-TxV1B4AN06683W\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n			<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n			I\'d like to use these to decorate our wedding reception.Can these be charged then used inside?Will they light up in our ballroom where it\'ll be lit?\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n			<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Yes, you can. There is an \"on and off\" button for power and a \"mode\' button for different style lighting. when I bought it in Dec, I left it outside for a few hours, and I brought it in to test for few hours then turned off. Now i just went checking on it in order to answer your question, I turned it on again, it still works. i am amazed that after four months of non-using there is still power inside.<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By MustLoveCats on April 29, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"TxV1B4AN06683W\"> </span> \r\n		</p>\r\n		<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n			<span>I would say probably not. It\'s hard to see their light when it is light out. But they are cheap enough where you could buy one a</span><span>nd </span><span>test it. They are beautiful!</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By D. Yahav on April 28, 2016</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Yes, they can be charged outside, and mine easily hold a charge for 10-12 hours at night. The lights are delicate looking and pretty, but not very bright. If you have a dimly lit area in your reception hall, they would be good for accent lighting, but would not really show in bright light. Also, I think they have a sensor--mine come on automatically at dusk out in my garden.&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n			<span style=\"color:#767676;font-size:13.3333px;\">By Amy Blake on May 1, 2016</span> \r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n			<br />\r\n		</p>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx19UBUXU08ZHH1\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Could&nbsp;I&nbsp;use&nbsp;the&nbsp;fairy&nbsp;lights&nbsp;indoor&nbsp;during&nbsp;the&nbsp;daytime?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>They are solar so they do need to charge in the sunlight. Once charged you can use them anywhere. They aren\'t bright enough to be effective other than at night, but you can put them in doors if you cover the solar panel. They are gorgeous outside at night. I put mine in a clear glass vase. Really pretty.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Pat Larson on April 26, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx19UBUXU08ZHH1\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx19UBUXU08ZHH1-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>I don\'t think so. They are solar and come on at dusk.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Elizabeth E. on April 26, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>in my experience, solar lights work better in the dark.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By tylinall on April 26, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx19UBUXU08ZHH1-2\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Of course</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Dee on April 26, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Yes u can. Don\'t laugh but what I do is face the solar part towards the wall or cover it up with something but don\'t forget it needs so light to get charged...amber</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amber J on May 2, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Possibly if it\'s dark, very dark and they were turned off the previous night so they held a charge...</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Melissa Perry on April 26, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>No, the lights come on automatically when it is DARK ONLY. Sorry.perhaps you could place them around a window, with the solar panel exposed to the sun and enjoy them at night.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By H. Christine Koenig on April 28, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n<br />\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1G3OJO050X0Z3\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				can you plug these into a wall?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>No - you can\'t plug them in. They are attached to a small solar panel.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Chris S. on November 15, 2015</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1IPNUBPTS85D6\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				What&nbsp;colors&nbsp;do&nbsp;this&nbsp;lights&nbsp;have&nbsp;？\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>Multi</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By no name on April 21, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx1IPNUBPTS85D6\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1IPNUBPTS85D6-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Multicolor. But you can set the lights to a single color or to change colors or flicker on and off. Just like Christmas lights. They are very nice lights and colorful.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By James S. on April 21, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:700;font-size:13.3333px;\">Question:</span> \r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1K3CV0JX64CPI\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				How long is the cord from the last light to the solar panel?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>the one i have is 21 ft and from solar panel to the first light is more than 3ft, i love this coz it gives bright lights at night</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Ellie on March 17, 2017</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx1K3CV0JX64CPI\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1K3CV0JX64CPI-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Over 3 ft</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Boozeandsailors on March 17, 2017</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>From solar panel to 1st light it\'s about 2 yards. From the first light to the last light it\'s about 5 yards. Hard to tell b/c I have them wound and twisted. But that\'s pretty close.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By wimbledon42 on March 21, 2017</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1PKWZI8AX42CO\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Can&nbsp;these&nbsp;fairy&nbsp;string&nbsp;lights&nbsp;be&nbsp;used&nbsp;in&nbsp;bedroom&nbsp;with&nbsp;the&nbsp;solar&nbsp;panel&nbsp;near&nbsp;the&nbsp;window?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>Yes asking as it gets sunlight</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Hai Juan Boeyinga on April 13, 2016</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1T56NGNXZZ23R\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				So the actual length of the lighted portion is about 14.5 \' if you subtract the 6.5\' (from 1st bulb to solar panel) from the advertised 21\', right?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>50 Colorful Flower Blossom LEDs of the light string is on a 21ft light strand (6.5ft lead cable included)</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Qedertek Direct&nbsp;SELLER&nbsp;<span class=\"a-letter-space\"></span>&nbsp;on December 15, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx1T56NGNXZZ23R\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1T56NGNXZZ23R-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Correct, the length is approximately 15 feet of lights and the other is the wire from the solar panel to the first light.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Jubilee on December 15, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Correct-I just measured mine for sure</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Ann &amp; Keith Mutz on December 22, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1V2RAIILU70PG\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Does each blossom change colors? Are all the blossoms the same color all at once?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>The blossoms do not change colors. They start at one end of the color spectrum and then gradually change the farther down the string of lights you go. They are not all the same color. Although they do make those these aren\'t that type</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on September 20, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx1V2RAIILU70PG\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1V2RAIILU70PG-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Yes</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Rheenchalets on September 20, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>yes, each blossom change colors</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By You &amp; Me Pet Shop on September 20, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>There are several settings - all on different colors, all blinking, alternate color blinking.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Patricia Melver on September 20, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx2357QDEP4E1UO\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Gow long is it and is it a bunch or on arrings?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>It\'s about 20 feet long and it\'s a long string! I love them in my garden</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on August 5, 2016</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx23XP8XE4612MD\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Does anyone have experience with these in a sukkah?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>Not sure what a sukksh is, I did Google it and near as I can figure it a wood frame. I stapled mine to our gazebo and they worked great.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Schellie Cavadini on October 28, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx23XP8XE4612MD\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx23XP8XE4612MD-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>As long as the solar gatherer is outside in the sun, it should be okay. You can\'t expect it to work with the solar gatherer inside.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By doro on October 28, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx24H8MJ0VCPAK4\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				I have 4 strands. I can charge all indoors using a plant light. I have not been able to charge them outdoors even after many hours of bright sunlight\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>If you have them pointed in the right direction, according to instructions, if they are getting the proper hours of sunlight, if the batteries are properly seated and the unit is switched on, there is no reason that they wouldn\'t charge.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Patty Kate\'s Mom on July 23, 2016</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx26XV9A0UP5V0U\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Can one connect several strands of these?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>No the have one solar panel each and no way to connect to each other as that\'s the strands individual power source.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By G. L. Frost on October 22, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx26XV9A0UP5V0U\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx26XV9A0UP5V0U-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>No. Each strand is wired to the solar panel that powers it. There\'s nothing to connect it to another strand.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on October 22, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>No, they are a self-contained unit.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Michelle Goldbeck on October 22, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>', 'Solar Powered Blossom Flower String Lights 50 LED Multi-color | Holiday Decorative Solar Flower String Lights - Qedertek', 'multi-color solar string lights, summer blossom flower solar string lights, LED blossom solar string lights,solar flower string lights', 'Wanna to shop multi-color solar string lights online, Qedertek is a professional led solar string lights supplier.This solar flower string lights,50 LED multi-color blossom designed, includes steady/flashing modes，IP65 waterproof, perfect for indoor and o', 'https://www.amazon.com/dp/B012VIRJ4I/', '', '0', '0.00', 'http://images.qedertek.com/59352d43a2a33', '{\"59352d43ba574\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352d43ba574\",\"59352d43da91e\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352d43da91e\",\"59352d4401f14\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352d4401f14\",\"59352d442ce37\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352d442ce37\"}', '0', '1', '0', '0.00', '1', '1491373319', '1496657220', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `qe_product` VALUES ('5', '2', 'Solar Waterproof Blossom Flower String Lights 50 LED Blue', '<span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Features</span><span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Solar powered led christmas lights, no utility energy costs&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Energy saving &amp; eco-friendly LED string lights, high energy conversion rate.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Lighting sensor technology, the string lights will light up automatically at dusk and may automatically turn off at daytime&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Specification</span><span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Light color: Blue&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Setting: Indoor/Outdoor&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">LED Quantity: 50 LEDs&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Solar Panel: 2V/100mA&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Battery type: Rechargeable 600mAH NI-MH Battery&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Light source: LED&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Switch: ON/OFF, MODE&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Working mode: Flash/Steady on&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Charging time: 6-8h&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Light length: 21ft(7m)&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Length between 2 blubs: 0.3ft(0.1m)&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Length from solar panel to first stake: 6.5ft(2m)&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Warm Tips</span><span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1. If the ground is too hard, try to soften the ground with water before you set up the solar panel&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">2. It is suggested the solar panel to be fully charged for 8h at the first use.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">3. Set up the solar panel at where there is enough sunshine with adjustable solar panel for direct sunlight&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">4. Turn the light on and set light mode before charging the solar power, so it will light up at dusk.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Warranty</span><span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">For any problem, please contact us at first, we will offer you a replacement or refund you.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">What\'s in the box</span><span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1 x Qedertek 50 LED Solar Christmas Lights&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1 x Solar Panel with Ground Stake&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1 x User Instruction</span>', '<ul class=\"a-unordered-list a-vertical a-spacing-none\" style=\"color:#949494;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Solar Powered Christmas lights: 50 blue flower blossoms on the 21ft light strand (6.5ft lead cable included), solar panel(2V/170mA) with built-in 600mA NI-MH AA rechargeable battery</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Long Working Time: Up to 8 hours of continuous lighting with a single battery fully charged</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Easy to Operate &amp; Install: Solar panel with 1 garden stake stand, 2 switches, On/Off and Mode (Steady/Flashing)</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Waterproof 50 LED Flower String Lights - Can withstand all kinds of weather, including heavy rain and snow</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Ideal for All Decorations - These wonderful string lights illuminate during night, adding warm and charming atmosphere to your home, garden, patio, lawn, porch, gate, yard, etc</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', '<br />', '50 LED Blue Solar Blossom String Lights,Outfit Amazing Christmas Lights,Special Blossom Light Design, Up to 8 Hours Working Time When Fully Charged - Qedertek', 'solar amazing christmas lights,blossom light decoration for party,decorative outfit flower string lights,blue blossom flower string lights', 'Blossom flower string lights, 50 LED flower shape blue lights, features IP65 waterproof, great for home, garden, patio, lawn, porch, gate, yard decorating, also good for indoor wedding house, xmas tree, bedroom ornament.', 'https://www.amazon.com/dp/B01EHP11RO/', '', '0', '0.00', 'http://images.qedertek.com/59352d92cd0f3', '{\"59352d92eb1a6\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352d92eb1a6\",\"59352d93176e3\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352d93176e3\",\"59352d9335eb4\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352d9335eb4\",\"59352d9361f46\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352d9361f46\"}', '0', '0', '0', '0.00', '1', '1491377975', '1496657299', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `qe_product` VALUES ('8', '2', 'Solar Powered Blossom String Lights 50 LED Cool White', '<p>\r\n	<img src=\"https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/aplus-seller-content-images-us-east-1/ATVPDKIKX0DER/A231TAZUOKNIOW/B012VIQPFM/9jY9UGDnRd2z._UX970_TTW_.jpg\" title=\"Solar Blossom Flower String Lights 50 LED White\" alt=\"Solar Blossom Flower String Lights 50 LED White\" /> \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\"><strong>Features</strong></span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Lights turn on automatically at Dusk</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Solar Powered, without utility energy costs</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Special peach blossom appearance makes your environment look out of ordinary</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">It is suggested the solar panel to be fully charged for 8h at the first use</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\"><strong>Specifications</strong></span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Light color: Cool white</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">LED Quantity: 50</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Rechargeable Ni-MH</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Battery: 1.2V 600mA</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Switch: Power ON/OFF, MODE</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Lighting Mode: Steady and 7 Blinking modes</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Solar Panel: 2V 100mA</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Charging Time: 6 hours</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Light Length: 21ft (7m)</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Length between 2 bulbs: 0.3ft (0.1m)</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Length from Solar panel to first stake: 6.5ft(2m)</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Solar panel with ground stake(8in) for easy positioning</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\"><strong>What\'s in the Box</strong></span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1 x Qedertek Solar String Lights</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1 x Solar Panel with Ground Stake</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1 x User Manual</span> \r\n</p>', '<ul class=\"a-unordered-list a-vertical a-spacing-none\" style=\"color:#949494;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Suitable for Indoor and Outdoor Decorations - These wonderful Christmas Lights illuminate during night, add a warm and charming atmosphere to your gardens, patio, lawn, porch, gate, yard, etc.</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Solar Powered Christmas Holiday Lights - Solar Panel and rechargeable battery, charge under sunlight and turns on automatically at dusk</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Super Long Working Time - Up to 8 hours of continuous lighting with a single battery charge</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Easy to Operate &amp; Install - Easy operation with 2 switch buttons( Power ON / OFF, MODE)</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Waterproof Flower Outdoor Lights - 21ft (6.5ft lead cable included) 50 LED outdoor lights can withstand all kinds of weather, including heavy rain and snow</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', '<div id=\"question-Tx11M4GX1YC6L23\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n			<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n			I just received two sets put them up in morning and now it\'s evening and they do not work . Direct sun for 8 hours. What could be problem?\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n			<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n			<span>There\'s an off and on switch on the solar panel...press it and see if they go on....</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Rosie Red on July 7, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx11M4GX1YC6L23\"> \r\n			<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx11M4GX1YC6L23-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n				<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n					<span>Please be sure you have the little switch set to \"on\"</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Bernard Ekdahl on July 8, 2016</span> \r\n				</div>\r\n				<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n					<span>Solar battery back with a switch button, please open.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Borlifes&nbsp;SELLER&nbsp;<span class=\"a-letter-space\"></span>&nbsp;on July 7, 2016</span> \r\n				</div>\r\n				<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n					<span>You must turn them on while charging them...</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Humita on July 8, 2016</span> \r\n				</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1913TB83X0OP\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				If I have no lights outside, will these provide some decent light to see on their own?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span class=\"askExpanderContainer askExpanderExpanded\"><span class=\"askLongText\">I use these on our hand railing to our porch-- we live in the country and cannot use bright lights or end up with bugs all over the place. These are bright enough to provide light to lead the way to porch and see the steps. No, it\'s not bright, white light and if you have vision problems it may not be suitable for what you are looking for.&nbsp;</span></span><br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Milissa on August 15, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx1913TB83X0OP\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1913TB83X0OP-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>No. They give off a soft blue light. They work amazingly well but not super bright</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By kchern on May 11, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Not unless you have quite a few of them</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By kellie sleesman on May 10, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1913TB83X0OP-2\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Yes ! The lights will last for as long as the battery has a charge. In other words if the day was sunny, you will have lights after dark longer than you will if the day was overcast.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on May 10, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Yes but very dim and depend on how long it has exposed to sun light.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Vu Nguyen on May 11, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1S8KQFHWJJ2RQ\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				how long is the lighted portion of the cable and how long is the entire cable?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>Sorry I can\'t give you the exact it\'s already hanging around the window but the package did indicate 21 feet of light. the space between the solar panels to the first light is around 3 feet sorry I can\'t be of more help</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By neddy on May 2, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx1S8KQFHWJJ2RQ\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1S8KQFHWJJ2RQ-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Not exactly sure of the entire length. The lighted portion is about 6\' - 8\' long.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Angelina on May 2, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>I think there is some clear space between the plug-in and the lighted portion (at least 7\' long). I can\'t remember, as these did not work inside (in a window), so I gave them away.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Laurel Berman on May 2, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1U7OOZF6UIBMS\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				If i put the solar cells on the dash of my car under my windshield, would it charge well?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>I think so</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on June 5, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx1U7OOZF6UIBMS\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1U7OOZF6UIBMS-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>I think so</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on June 5, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>probably they charge really fast in our yard</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By mike stone on June 6, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Probably, if your car is in the light. However, be aware the extra heat may shorten the lifespan on the battery.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By SweetSoulX on June 11, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx2VETT1Z5MWXHR\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Hi. So if the light are set up inside my house, how would i charge the solar panel? Is the solar panel detachable?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>Solar panel is not detachable.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on October 18, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx2VETT1Z5MWXHR\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx2VETT1Z5MWXHR-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span class=\"askExpanderContainer askExpanderExpanded\"><span class=\"askLongText\">I suppose you could place the solar panel in a sunny window; that might work. The string of lights ends with a length of just wire for about 2 feet and then the collector which is on a stick. My lights are outside around a potted Colorado Blue Spruce with the collector jabbed into a neighboring pot. Hope this is helpful.</span></span><br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By L. Larchyk on October 18, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx302JXNYYX9CFA\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Can the plastic flower light be pulled off and then re attached? Want to use in a craft project.\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>Yes the plastic flower can be removed from the light. Good luck in your project, got my wheels turning too.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on November 22, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx302JXNYYX9CFA\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx302JXNYYX9CFA-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Doesn\'t seem like it, but I haven\'t tried so I\'m not completely positive</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Marie on November 22, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>i think it all in one piece</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By doro on November 22, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx37IX4M2OGXXV1\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				If i put the solar cells on the dash of my car under my windshield, would it charge well?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>It should. I use mine for my patio and I put the panel on the roof. The lights go all night long!</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By vinluan5 on June 6, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx37IX4M2OGXXV1\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx37IX4M2OGXXV1-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Yes, but make sure the switch is on, other ways it will not charge!</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Humita on June 7, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>It might depend on how much tint you have in your windshield! Why not try it? Fun experiment. Let us know what happens.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Deb on June 7, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-TxRNFMXDVUJ3EN\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Do they charge indoors\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>I don\'t know, they\'re designed for solar exposure</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on December 1, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"TxRNFMXDVUJ3EN\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-TxRNFMXDVUJ3EN-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>No the charge in only solar light.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By G. L. Frost on December 1, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>They don\'t plug in, they need sunlight to charge</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Lynn Lake on December 1, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-TxRNFMXDVUJ3EN-2\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>If the solar panel is near a window with bright light, yes.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Christi Morris on December 1, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Im not sure if they will. I had mine outside in direct sunlight for days and they failed to charge. Maybe I had a bad batch I dont know.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By ashley on December 1, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>I would imagine in a window with a lot of light they would charge. They are purely solar so not battery charged.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Sara M on December 2, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n<br />\r\n</div>', 'Solar String Lights: 50 LED Blossom String Lights,Flower Garden Light Decorations，Festival Led Lights - Qedertek', 'blossom garden light decorations,backyard hanging solar string lights,festival led lights,cool white blossom lights,50 LED solar string lights', 'If you are looking for flower garden lights，don\'t miss this cool white blossom lights，solar powered，waterproof, easy to pperate & install, waterproof, fit all weather, including heavy rain and snow, great for outdoor lighting decor.', 'https://www.amazon.com/dp/B012VIQPFM/', '', '0', '0.00', 'http://images.qedertek.com/59352dc1dc6cf', '{\"59352dc1f1a3a\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352dc1f1a3a\",\"59352dc236a2e\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352dc236a2e\",\"59352dc24d717\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352dc24d717\",\"59352dc274260\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352dc274260\"}', '0', '1', '0', '0.00', '1', '1491379426', '1496657346', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `qe_product` VALUES ('9', '2', 'Solar Powered Cherry Blossom String Lights 50 LED Pink', '<span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Note: The solar panel must remain directly facing sunlight for a whole day to conserve sufficient solar power before its first use. Plus, to ensure sufficient solar energy to be stored for the lights to function smoothly in winter, panel should be fully exposed to sunlight as well.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Features:</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1.Solar Powered LED, no utility energy costs incurred.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">2.It is suggested the solar panel to be fully charged for 6hrs before its first use.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\"><br />\r\nSpecification:</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1.Light color: Purple.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">2.Lights Total: 50 LED.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">3.Rechargeable Ni-MH Battery: 2V 600mA.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">4.Switch Buttons: Power ON/OFF and MODE.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">5.Lighting Modes: Constant ON / Flashing.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">6.Charging Time: 6 hours.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">7.Total Length: 22.9ft (7m).&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">8.Bulb Spacing: 0.3ft (0.1m).&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">9.Leading Cable Length: 6.5ft (2m).&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">10.Solar panel with a ground stake for easy positioning.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\"><br />\r\nHow the solar panel works:</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;1.During the daytime, solar panel converses solar energy and converts it to electrical energy.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">2.The battery releases the energy as lighting power when it\'s dark.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">3.A Ni-MH AA rechargeable battery in solar box is durable.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">What\'s in the Box:</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1x50 LED Fairy Solar Blossom String Lights&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1xGround Stake&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1xSolar Panel&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1xUser Manual</span>', '<ul class=\"a-unordered-list a-vertical a-spacing-none\" style=\"color:#949494;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Elegant outdoor d¨¦cor - the Pink blossom is attractive for your landscape, it can be a precious gift for your friends and families.</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Useful &amp; Safe - it can serve multiple purposes, e.g. night lighting, gifts, home decor,commercial promo. Its low working voltage is safe to use for family with children</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Solar &amp; Durable - it is cost - saving and eco friendly. The waterproof led lights of strong glass and hard material are erosion - resistant. The rechargeable battery can work up to 8hrs.</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Easy installation &amp; Auto - the solar panel can be easily installed and works automatically with solar energy. One button\'s for power controlling and the other mode controlling.</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Recommended Uses: home, patio, lawn, garden, swing, hammock, tree house, pavillion, pergola, balcony, roof ceiling, bars, walkway, shops.</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', '<div id=\"question-Tx123H38531NBA8\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n			<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n			Does the ammount of charge affect the brightness of the lights?\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n			<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n			<span>Mine stay on all night and don\'t see much of a change of brightness.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By ElChuck on December 23, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx123H38531NBA8\"> \r\n			<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx123H38531NBA8-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n				<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n					<span>Yes but in my experience it doesn\'t end up as bright as lights with an actual connection to power. That is just fine with me.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Cate F. on December 23, 2016</span> \r\n				</div>\r\n				<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n					<span>Yes. If it is a cloudy day, they are very dim or might not come on at all. A sunny day, you get a few hours of decent light.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By nicole smith on December 24, 2016</span> \r\n				</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n			<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx123H38531NBA8-2\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n				<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n					<span>Yes it does. It would be ideal to make sure the unit catches sunlight all day for better luminescence at night.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on December 23, 2016</span> \r\n				</div>\r\n				<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n					<span>I don\'t think so, it\'s the style not brightness, thanks!</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By beautiful springs on December 23, 2016</span> \r\n				</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1EEL1KECX8EZL\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				People who bought these a while ago, is it still working good for you? I am trying to know how long do the lights themselves live for\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>I started using them in spring and they are still going strong. I believe there is a battery for the mode changes but the lights are all solar power. So far so good.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By J. N. McCarthy on September 11, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx1EEL1KECX8EZL\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1EEL1KECX8EZL-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>yes, they still work. I love these lights. they are bright and stay lit for a long time! if they stop working you can replace the batteries and Amazon sellso them.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By L. Tweet on September 11, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>I just put them about a wk ago the lights will last til morning before the sunrise</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Mrs. RoxG on September 11, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1LZTD2YECNJCC\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				anyone living in upstate ny..does the battery get sufficiently recharged on those long cloudy winter days?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>It does to my surprise. May take a little longer to charge but definitely still charges!</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on October 26, 2016</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1RES7WTLUKQR3\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				is it solar powered?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>Yes, ours is. The solar unit powers a small battery pack which has its own stand, a stake for the ground and a slot to attach it.<br />\r\nJay</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Jay Fluck on November 17, 2015</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx1RES7WTLUKQR3\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1RES7WTLUKQR3-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Supposed to be. Yes</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Jay Fluck on November 18, 2015</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1X53JCIJQTJHA\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				How large are the flowers?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>About the size of a quarter.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Marc Morency on March 8, 2017</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx1X53JCIJQTJHA\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1X53JCIJQTJHA-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>They are on the small side, I\'d say less than an inch diameter. Also, mine only worked twice, and I waited too long to return them.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Alicia Davis on March 9, 2017</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>1.5 inch diameter</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By maoyuma on March 7, 2017</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1X53JCIJQTJHA-2\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>I haven\'t measured them but they look to be about an inch in diameter. Hope that helped.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Susan K. Davis on March 7, 2017</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>The flowers are about 3/4 of an inch in diameter.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on March 9, 2017</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1YRV2DPGPM2XZ\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				The battery inclued?? yes or no\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>If you\'re asking about that small solar panel yes, its included.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Minnie Me on November 17, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx1YRV2DPGPM2XZ\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1YRV2DPGPM2XZ-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Solar energy, do not need batteries</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By evona on November 17, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>This is solar powered. There is no battery. It even charges in cloudy days.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Jamie Gath on November 18, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Solar. No battery.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on November 18, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx21XCNMCSG70R\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Does the solar panel need direct sunlight to get powered?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>Yes, at least 6 to 8 hrs</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on April 5, 2016</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx24CCGO3BGEGA5\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				what size is each flower?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>About 1 inch.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Elena on April 15, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx24CCGO3BGEGA5\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx24CCGO3BGEGA5-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>About one inch, maybe 1 and 1 1/2 inch.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By CylePsycho on April 12, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Dear , each flower is 1.2 inch for its diameter.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Qedertek Direct&nbsp;SELLER&nbsp;<span class=\"a-letter-space\"></span>&nbsp;on April 13, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx258WH2IQ263NR\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				how long is the cord from solar box to first light?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>1 meter</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Ivan M. on December 31, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx258WH2IQ263NR\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx258WH2IQ263NR-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Excelente duracion</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Sandel Manuel Encarnacion Cuev… on December 31, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx283GCCTO9ZDKR\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Dose it get solar charged when switch it off position? how can i set it to charge without turning switch on?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>I believe the switch always stays on. I chose the sequence I wanted and have always left it on since I set them up.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By claudia on April 4, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx283GCCTO9ZDKR\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx283GCCTO9ZDKR-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>I think that it can not be charged in \"off\" position. However, when you charge it in \"on\" position and there is enough light the sensor does not allow the battery to discharge. S oI never had that kind of problem</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Vsevolod S. on April 4, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx2B6EBAK5DTHY1\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Can I charge during the day, turn off when I leave so they don\'t waste before I am home, and then turn on at night with a full charge?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span class=\"askExpanderContainer askExpanderExpanded\"><span class=\"askLongText\">Not by itself. There is a Power off and on button. There is also an Auto Button, if you want it to turn on by itself when it gets dark. So use the Power on an off button when you want it, lets say you come home and want it on for 2 hours then you can go and switch it off if you do not want it on anymore. Hope this is clear. if any questions let me know.</span></span><br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Elena on March 23, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx2B6EBAK5DTHY1\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx2B6EBAK5DTHY1-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Yes you can turn it on and off too or let it on automatic.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Elena on March 22, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span class=\"askExpanderContainer askExpanderExpanded\"><span class=\"askLongText\">I bought these to put around the outer edge of my fairy garden. I haven\'t actually put it together yet. But I have other fairy solar lights on my pergula. To my knowledge there is no turn off/on switch on these type of inexpensive string lights to use all the time. Once you turn the switch on it stays on. If you turn off the memory will turn the lights off BUT they won\'t charge either. Atleast that\'s the way I understand the operating instructions. Hope this helps =)</span></span><br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on March 27, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx2B6EBAK5DTHY1-2\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Yes it charges in the OFF position too. This has nothing to do with the battery charging. The on and OFF button is just for you to turn on or off the lights.<br />\r\nMake sure the battery will be placed so it gets sun most of the day. It can be even inside the house or the windowsill.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Elena on March 23, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span class=\"askExpanderContainer askExpanderExpanded\"><span class=\"askLongText\">Yes it charges, as the solar battery does not need to be turned on or off, it is just the battery that charges with the sun. The on and off button is just to turn the lights on or off, meaning to use the batteries energy that has been saved during the day. You would need to have the battery positioned so it gets most sun light in the day. On cloudy days it will not have that much sun and the lights may not last that long in the evening, but if sunny they lights last many hours.</span></span><br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Elena on March 23, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx2CJ5JQQXCOV33\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Can these be left ON all the time? Will they recharge that way or do they have to be turned off each night?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>I leave them on everyday. They will recharge via sunlight. They work wonderful and come each night.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Angel on April 5, 2016</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>', 'Best Solar Powered 50 LED Pink Cherry String Lights | Solar Outdoor Pink Blossom Party Lights Backyard - Qedertek', 'holiday cherry light bulbs string,blossom lighting and home decor,solar outdoor party lights backyard,pink blossom string lights,pink flower Led solar string lights', 'Holiday string lights, cherry blossom lighting exterior designed, waterproof, solar powered great for pavillion, pergola, roof ceiling, walkway adorning, also good for children room ornament.', 'https://www.amazon.com/dp/B01IN9FR5M/', '', '0', '0.00', 'http://images.qedertek.com/59352e2982071', '{\"59352de2c7233\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352de2c7233\",\"59352de310ab6\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352de310ab6\",\"59352de34958d\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352de34958d\",\"59352de371546\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352de371546\",\"59352e29a24dd\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352e29a24dd\",\"59352e29bd567\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352e29bd567\",\"59352e29db390\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352e29db390\",\"59352e2a23d0d\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352e2a23d0d\"}', '0', '0', '0', '0.00', '1', '1491382827', '1499046091', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `qe_product` VALUES ('10', '2', 'Solar Powered 50-LED Purple Blossom Flower String Lights', '<span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Note: The solar panel must remain directly facing sunlight for a whole day to conserve sufficient solar power before its first use. Plus, to ensure sufficient solar energy to be stored for the lights to function smoothly in winter, panel should be fully exposed to sunlight as well.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Features:</span><span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Solar powered, without utility energy costs&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Special peach blossom appearance makes your environment look out of ordinary&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n</span> \r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\"><span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">It is suggested the solar panel to be fully charged for 8hrs at the first use.&nbsp;</span></span> \r\n</p>\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\"><span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Specifications:</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Light color: Purple&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">LED Quantity: 50 LED&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Rechargeable Ni-MH Battery: 1.2V 600mA&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Switch: Power ON/OFF, MODE&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Lighting Mode: Steady and 7 Blinking modes&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Solar Panel: 2V 100mA&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Charging Time: 6 hours&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Light Length: 21ft (7m)&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Length between 2 blubs: 0.3ft (0.1m)&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Length from Solar panel to first stake: 6.5ft(2m)&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Solar panel with ground stake(8in) for easy positioning&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">What\'s in the Box:</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1 x Qedertek Solar String Lights&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1 x Solar Panel with Ground Stake&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1 x User Instruction</span></span><span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\"></span>', '<ul class=\"a-unordered-list a-vertical a-spacing-none\" style=\"color:#949494;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Elegant outdoor d¨¦cor - the purple blossom is attractive for your landscape, it can be a precious gift for your friends and families.</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Useful &amp; Safe - it can serve multiple purposes, e.g. night lighting, gifts, home decor,commercial promo. Its low working voltage is safe to use for family with children</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Solar &amp; Durable - it is cost - saving and eco friendly. The waterproof led lights of strong glass and hard material are erosion - resistant. The rechargeable battery can work up to 8hrs.</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Easy installation &amp; Auto - the solar panel can be easily installed and works automatically with solar energy. One button\'s for power controlling and the other mode controlling.</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Recommended Uses: home, patio, lawn, garden, swing, hammock, tree house, pavillion, pergola, balcony, roof ceiling, bars, walkway, shops.</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', '<div id=\"question-Tx123H38531NBA8\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color:#111111;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n			<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n			Does the ammount of charge affect the brightness of the lights?\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color:#111111;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n			<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n			<span>Mine stay on all night and don\'t see much of a change of brightness.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By ElChuck on December 23, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx123H38531NBA8\"> \r\n			<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx123H38531NBA8-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n					<span>Yes but in my experience it doesn\'t end up as bright as lights with an actual connection to power. That is just fine with me.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Cate F. on December 23, 2016</span> \r\n				</div>\r\n				<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n					<span>Yes. If it is a cloudy day, they are very dim or might not come on at all. A sunny day, you get a few hours of decent light.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By nicole smith on December 24, 2016</span> \r\n				</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n			<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx123H38531NBA8-2\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n					<span>Yes it does. It would be ideal to make sure the unit catches sunlight all day for better luminescence at night.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on December 23, 2016</span> \r\n				</div>\r\n				<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n					<span>I don\'t think so, it\'s the style not brightness, thanks!</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By beautiful springs on December 23, 2016</span> \r\n				</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1EEL1KECX8EZL\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				People who bought these a while ago, is it still working good for you? I am trying to know how long do the lights themselves live for\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div 