5-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>About one inch, maybe 1 and 1 1/2 inch.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By CylePsycho on April 12, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>Dear , each flower is 1.2 inch for its diameter.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Qedertek Direct&nbsp;SELLER&nbsp;<span class=\"a-letter-space\"></span>&nbsp;on April 13, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx258WH2IQ263NR\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				how long is the cord from solar box to first light?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span>1 meter</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Ivan M. on December 31, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx258WH2IQ263NR\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx258WH2IQ263NR-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>Excelente duracion</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Sandel Manuel Encarnacion Cuev… on December 31, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx283GCCTO9ZDKR\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				Dose it get solar charged when switch it off position? how can i set it to charge without turning switch on?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span>I believe the switch always stays on. I chose the sequence I wanted and have always left it on since I set them up.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By claudia on April 4, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx283GCCTO9ZDKR\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx283GCCTO9ZDKR-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>I think that it can not be charged in \"off\" position. However, when you charge it in \"on\" position and there is enough light the sensor does not allow the battery to discharge. S oI never had that kind of problem</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Vsevolod S. on April 4, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx2B6EBAK5DTHY1\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				Can I charge during the day, turn off when I leave so they don\'t waste before I am home, and then turn on at night with a full charge?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"askExpanderContainer askExpanderExpanded\">Not by itself. There is a Power off and on button. There is also an Auto Button, if you want it to turn on by itself when it gets dark. So use the Power on an off button when you want it, lets say you come home and want it on for 2 hours then you can go and switch it off if you do not want it on anymore. Hope this is clear. if any questions let me know.</span><br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Elena on March 23, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx2B6EBAK5DTHY1\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx2B6EBAK5DTHY1-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>Yes you can turn it on and off too or let it on automatic.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Elena on March 22, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span class=\"askExpanderContainer askExpanderExpanded\">I bought these to put around the outer edge of my fairy garden. I haven\'t actually put it together yet. But I have other fairy solar lights on my pergula. To my knowledge there is no turn off/on switch on these type of inexpensive string lights to use all the time. Once you turn the switch on it stays on. If you turn off the memory will turn the lights off BUT they won\'t charge either. Atleast that\'s the way I understand the operating instructions. Hope this helps =)</span><br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on March 27, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx2B6EBAK5DTHY1-2\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>Yes it charges in the OFF position too. This has nothing to do with the battery charging. The on and OFF button is just for you to turn on or off the lights.<br />\r\nMake sure the battery will be placed so it gets sun most of the day. It can be even inside the house or the windowsill.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Elena on March 23, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span class=\"askExpanderContainer askExpanderExpanded\">Yes it charges, as the solar battery does not need to be turned on or off, it is just the battery that charges with the sun. The on and off button is just to turn the lights on or off, meaning to use the batteries energy that has been saved during the day. You would need to have the battery positioned so it gets most sun light in the day. On cloudy days it will not have that much sun and the lights may not last that long in the evening, but if sunny they lights last many hours.</span><br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Elena on March 23, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx2CJ5JQQXCOV33\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				Can these be left ON all the time? Will they recharge that way or do they have to be turned off each night?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span>I leave them on everyday. They will recharge via sunlight. They work wonderful and come each night.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Angel on April 5, 2016</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>', 'Solar Fairy Lights 50 LED Blossom Home Light Decor | Warm White Flower Birthday Lights Decorations - Qedertek', 'home light decorations,decorative string,birthday lights decorations,solar string fairy lights,blossom flower string fairy lights', 'Wanna to shop birthday lights decorations online, Qedertek is a professional home light decorations supplier,the blossom flower string fairy lights,cute blossom design, solar operated,with lighting sensor, auto on/off, which would be you best choice.', 'https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0135O1TWA/', '', '0', '0.00', 'http://images.qedertek.com/59352e82ab0b7', '{\"59352e82d7611\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352e82d7611\",\"59352e8306eee\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352e8306eee\",\"59352e8329d89\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352e8329d89\",\"59352e8356099\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352e8356099\"}', '0', 