\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n			<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n			<span>about the diameter of a quarter</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Patricia F Johnson on December 8, 2015</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx15LMVYMPT13Y1\"> \r\n			<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx15LMVYMPT13Y1-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n				<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n					<span>About the size of cherries.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Chico and Jenn on October 2, 2016</span> \r\n				</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx119X76UNOU7N2\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Can the solar panel charge in cloudy or winter?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span class=\"askExpanderContainer askExpanderExpanded\"><span class=\"askLongText\">Just bought mine a few weeks ago so I don\'t know about winter, but imagine it\'d be similar to cloudy days or days without long periods of sun. It charges but then the power draws down earlier, so the lights won\'t last all night. Thus far, the lights still have power when I go to sleep by 11 pm but depending on how sunny it was the day before, the lights may or may not be on when I wake up before 6am.</span></span><br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By betty on April 19, 2016</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1QMMEL6OZ2WRQ\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Auto working at night?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>They are awesome. Come on at sundown and stay on until until about 3 a.m. The round bulbs work better than the little flower ones.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Kimberlee Kay on November 30, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx1QMMEL6OZ2WRQ\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1QMMEL6OZ2WRQ-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Yes, if you have placed the solar panel in a position to receive sunlight to charge, and have turned on the \"ON\" button or \"\"POWER\" button. I\'m not sure which it says. Remember, if it has been lit for 8 or more hours, it needs to recharge. Cloudy days do not allow that. I hope this helps.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Catherine on November 30, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx3Q13E6R4FSFHP\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				I live in Washington . There isn\'t a ton of sun...will it be enough to power these?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>I believe so. We\'ve had many raining overcast days since putting these out and they have been glowing each evening nicely.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Nancy J on May 17, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx3Q13E6R4FSFHP\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx3Q13E6R4FSFHP-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>I think so. They are really great.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Valeriya on May 17, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Yes you should be very pleased with these lights .I love them.Even on overcast days, they work well.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Sandra A. on May 17, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>I live in Seattle and they light up well each night. I am actually amazed at how long they hold a charge too.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By acwink on May 17, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-TxVLPKUIKSTUL2\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Will these keep the lighting mode from day to day? I purchased a different set and they reset to the first \"flashy mode\" every evening.\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>Mine do not need resetting</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By jaycee on March 31, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"TxVLPKUIKSTUL2\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-TxVLPKUIKSTUL2-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Our experience with the ones we bought kept whatever \"frequency\" you chose from the day before.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By JD on April 1, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Yes, mine do.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Lee on March 31, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-TxVLPKUIKSTUL2-2\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>They stay on one sold light the good thing is they are solor powdered</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Jeana KING on March 31, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>No, once I set it to the mode I wanted. I didn\'t need to change it ever.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Azuki-chan on April 1, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-TxVLPKUIKSTUL2-2\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>They stay on one sold light the good thing is they are solor powdered</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Jeana KING on March 31, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>No, once I set it to the mode I wanted. I didn\'t need to change it ever.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Azuki-chan on April 1, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx12LUIELJ4YJUP\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				How do you tell if the switch is on when you initially charge? Mine did not come with instructions\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>There\'s two buttons in the back that say \"mode\". They have to sit in the sunlight for a while for them to work . Make sure you take the plastic that is on there to protect the solar thing. Leave them out in the sun for a day and at night turn the mode on and you will see how they glow !!!</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Jen Miller on July 9, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx12LUIELJ4YJUP\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx12LUIELJ4YJUP-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>I just waited till dusk and put my hand over the solar panel and proceeded to depress the on off button till they lighted .</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Nancy J on July 9, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx13TXLH8AZAOJS\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Will they work indoors like in a bedroom.\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>the solar panel needs some light to charge the battery</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By james p gidusko on June 7, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx13TXLH8AZAOJS\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx13TXLH8AZAOJS-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Yes-if u make sure they get sun on the charger all day.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By R. Homeyer-Bente on June 7, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx17QWZTVP2VMUH\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Does the panel come with a mounting bracket so that you can attach and start the string higher up in the tree?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>No, it\'s does not.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Lee on May 9, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx17QWZTVP2VMUH\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx17QWZTVP2VMUH-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>The panel comes with a bracket that attaches to a small stake you can put in the ground. You might be able to attach the bracket to a tree, but it doesn\'t appear to be for that purpose. Remember that your panel needs to be in the sun to charge. Keep it out of the shade as much as possible. Enjoy your solar lights!</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on May 10, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1DDGOL2T1SVDH\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Do you need more than on solar panel for multiple strands?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>Each strand comes with a solar panel.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By acwink on June 2, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx1DDGOL2T1SVDH\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1DDGOL2T1SVDH-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Each strand comes with its own attached solar panel.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Nancy J on June 3, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>I m not sure what you are trying to ask. Every string comes with everything you need.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Valeriya on June 2, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1DDGOL2T1SVDH-2\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Yes....each strand has it\'s own solar panel</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Sandra A. on June 2, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>The one.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Blue lighting&nbsp;on June 2, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1MN520ZTJ62SR\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				How does one replace the rechargeable battery? And where do we get these batteries? Had several sets that were working but now seem dim even charged.\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>The rechargeable battery is in the solar panel case. The directions said to just open it and replace the battery. I have not had to do that though. Maybe contact the seller. Sorry to hear about your issue!</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By B. Bollen on September 21, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx1MN520ZTJ62SR\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1MN520ZTJ62SR-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>The Qedertek globe solar string lights with built in 1pcs rechargeable NI-MH AA battery(1.2v/600mA). In general, we didn\'t suggest the customer replace the battery, we suggest you to charge the battery in direct sunlight up to 8h to ensure the battery get fully charged.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Qedertek Direct&nbsp;on September 22, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>when you check out the price of the batteries, you will probably just wanna get a new set of lights....also, looks like you are in the NW probably not enough sunlight to charge fully.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By BEACH BABY on September 21, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1UEYYDYW44BA9\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Does the solar panel need direct sunlight to get powered?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>Yes, it does.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Azuki-chan on April 20, 2016</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1V10KHQVH1YHT\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Do they use rechargable by the sun bateries? if so, what kind aa or aaa?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>Mine run on one AA NiCad rechargeable. I had some several years ago and I love them. I recently bought several more and the price is much cheaper now than when I bought the first few sets.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By John M. on March 28, 2017</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx1V10KHQVH1YHT\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1V10KHQVH1YHT-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>No batteries needed at all. They have a solar panel with a post to put in the ground. Charge in the sun for eight hours and they are good to go. Very easy to use. Nice light. They are great so far.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Jalapeño 023 on March 24, 2017</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>There are no batteries. The strand of lights have a small solar panel attached at one end that can be attached to a stake or simply hung facing the sun. Handsfree!</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on March 29, 2017</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n<br />\r\n</div>', 'Multi-color 30 LED Crystal Ball String Lights | Solar Powered Outdoor Christmas Decorating Globe Lights- Qedertek', 'crystal ball string lights,outdoor christmas decorating ball lights,room decor with globe lights,decorating with solar string lights, multi-color solar globe string lights', 'Outdoor Christmas decorating ball lights, solar powered, multi-color globe design, Great for home and outdoor decorations, Also good for party lighting decorating.', 'https://www.amazon.com/dp/B01DPCKFRW/', '', '0', '0.00', 'http://images.qedertek.com/59352edb8ad08', '{\"59352edbb2d33\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352edbb2d33\",\"59352edbda983\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352edbda983\",\"59352edc0498a\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352edc0498a\",\"59352edc1dad6\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352edc1dad6\"}', '0', '1', '0', '0.00', '1', '1491445621', '1496657628', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `qe_product` VALUES ('15', '2', 'Solar Powered Crystal Ball String Lights 30 LED Warm White ', '<span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#333333;font-weight:700;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Features:</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#333333;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Solar powered LED, no utility energy costs&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#333333;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Charges even on cloudy days, turns on at dusk automatically&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#333333;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Easy for installation and maintenance&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#333333;font-weight:700;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Specifications:</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#333333;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">LED Color: Warm White</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#333333;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">LED Quantity: 30 LED&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#333333;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Rechargeable Ni-MH Battery: 1.2V 600mA&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#333333;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Switch: Power ON/OFF &amp; MODE&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#333333;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Lighting Mode: Steady ON / Flashing&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#333333;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Solar Panel: 2V 100mA&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#333333;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Charging Time: 6 hours&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#333333;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Light Length: 19.7ft (6m), 5ft lead cable included&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#333333;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Length between 2 bulbs: 0.5ft (0.15m)&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#333333;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Length from Solar panel to first stake: 5ft (1.5m)&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#333333;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Solar panel with ground stake for easy positioning&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#333333;font-weight:700;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Warm Tips:&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#333333;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Solar Light will have best performance, when you place it in a sunny area or an area with direct sun most of the day time.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#333333;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">To get better performance, we recommend 100% charged before your fist use.&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#333333;font-weight:700;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">What\'s in the box:</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#333333;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1 x Qedertek Globe String Lights&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#333333;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1 x Solar Panel with Ground Stake&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#333333;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1 x User Manual</span>', '<ul class=\"a-unordered-list a-vertical a-spacing-none\" style=\"color:#949494;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Dusk to dawn sensor: solar powered and rechargeable battery, turn on at dusk automatically</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Long working time: up to 8 hours of continuous lighting with a&nbsp;single battery fully charged, it even charges on cloudy winter days</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Flashing &amp; steady on modes: 2 switch buttons- power on/off, 8 mode switch</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Ip65 waterproof: can withstand all kinds of weather, including heavy rain and snow, perfect for indoor and outdoor decoration</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Suitable for indoor and outdoor: these wonderful outdoor string lights illuminate during night, add warm and charming atmosphere to your gardens</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', '<div id=\"question-Tx15LMVYMPT13Y1\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color:#111111;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n			<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n			How big around are the lights themselves?\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color:#111111;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n			<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n			<span>about the diameter of a quarter</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Patricia F Johnson on December 8, 2015</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx15LMVYMPT13Y1\"> \r\n			<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx15LMVYMPT13Y1-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n					<span>About the size of cherries.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Chico and Jenn on October 2, 2016</span> \r\n				</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx119X76UNOU7N2\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				Can the solar panel charge in cloudy or winter?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"askExpanderContainer askExpanderExpanded\">Just bought mine a few weeks ago so I don\'t know about winter, but imagine it\'d be similar to cloudy days or days without long periods of sun. It charges but then the power draws down earlier, so the lights won\'t last all night. Thus far, the lights still have power when I go to sleep by 11 pm but depending on how sunny it was the day before, the lights may or may not be on when I wake up before 6am.</span><br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By betty on April 19, 2016</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1QMMEL6OZ2WRQ\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				Auto working at night?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span>They are awesome. Come on at sundown and stay on until until about 3 a.m. The round bulbs work better than the little flower ones.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Kimberlee Kay on November 30, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx1QMMEL6OZ2WRQ\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1QMMEL6OZ2WRQ-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>Yes, if you have placed the solar panel in a position to receive sunlight to charge, and have turned on the \"ON\" button or \"\"POWER\" button. I\'m not sure which it says. Remember, if it has been lit for 8 or more hours, it needs to recharge. Cloudy days do not allow that. I hope this helps.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Catherine on November 30, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx3Q13E6R4FSFHP\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				I live in Washington . There isn\'t a ton of sun...will it be enough to power these?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span>I believe so. We\'ve had many raining overcast days since putting these out and they have been glowing each evening nicely.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Nancy J on May 17, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx3Q13E6R4FSFHP\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx3Q13E6R4FSFHP-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>I think so. They are really great.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Valeriya on May 17, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>Yes you should be very pleased with these lights .I love them.Even on overcast days, they work well.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Sandra A. on May 17, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>I live in Seattle and they light up well each night. I am actually amazed at how long they hold a charge too.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By acwink on May 17, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-TxVLPKUIKSTUL2\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				Will these keep the lighting mode from day to day? I purchased a different set and they reset to the first \"flashy mode\" every evening.\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span>Mine do not need resetting</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By jaycee on March 31, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"TxVLPKUIKSTUL2\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-TxVLPKUIKSTUL2-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>Our experience with the ones we bought kept whatever \"frequency\" you chose from the day before.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By JD on April 1, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>Yes, mine do.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Lee on March 31, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-TxVLPKUIKSTUL2-2\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>They stay on one sold light the good thing is they are solor powdered</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Jeana KING on March 31, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>No, once I set it to the mode I wanted. I didn\'t need to change it ever.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Azuki-chan on April 1, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-TxVLPKUIKSTUL2-2\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>They stay on one sold light the good thing is they are solor powdered</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Jeana KING on March 31, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>No, once I set it to the mode I wanted. I didn\'t need to change it ever.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Azuki-chan on April 1, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx12LUIELJ4YJUP\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				How do you tell if the switch is on when you initially charge? Mine did not come with instructions\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span>There\'s two buttons in the back that say \"mode\". They have to sit in the sunlight for a while for them to work . Make sure you take the plastic that is on there to protect the solar thing. Leave them out in the sun for a day and at night turn the mode on and you will see how they glow !!!</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Jen Miller on July 9, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx12LUIELJ4YJUP\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx12LUIELJ4YJUP-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>I just waited till dusk and put my hand over the solar panel and proceeded to depress the on off button till they lighted .</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Nancy J on July 9, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx13TXLH8AZAOJS\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				Will they work indoors like in a bedroom.\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span>the solar panel needs some light to charge the battery</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By james p gidusko on June 7, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx13TXLH8AZAOJS\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx13TXLH8AZAOJS-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>Yes-if u make sure they get sun on the charger all day.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By R. Homeyer-Bente on June 7, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx17QWZTVP2VMUH\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				Does the panel come with a mounting bracket so that you can attach and start the string higher up in the tree?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span>No, it\'s does not.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Lee on May 9, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx17QWZTVP2VMUH\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx17QWZTVP2VMUH-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>The panel comes with a bracket that attaches to a small stake you can put in the ground. You might be able to attach the bracket to a tree, but it doesn\'t appear to be for that purpose. Remember that your panel needs to be in the sun to charge. Keep it out of the shade as much as possible. Enjoy your solar lights!</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on May 10, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1DDGOL2T1SVDH\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				Do you need more than on solar panel for multiple strands?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span>Each strand comes with a solar panel.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By acwink on June 2, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx1DDGOL2T1SVDH\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1DDGOL2T1SVDH-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>Each strand comes with its own attached solar panel.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Nancy J on June 3, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>I m not sure what you are trying to ask. Every string comes with everything you need.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Valeriya on June 2, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1DDGOL2T1SVDH-2\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>Yes....each strand has it\'s own solar panel</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Sandra A. on June 2, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>The one.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Blue lighting&nbsp;on June 2, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1MN520ZTJ62SR\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				How does one replace the rechargeable battery? And where do we get these batteries? Had several sets that were working but now seem dim even charged.\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span>The rechargeable battery is in the solar panel case. The directions said to just open it and replace the battery. I have not had to do that though. Maybe contact the seller. Sorry to hear about your issue!</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By B. Bollen on September 21, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx1MN520ZTJ62SR\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1MN520ZTJ62SR-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>The Qedertek globe solar string lights with built in 1pcs rechargeable NI-MH AA battery(1.2v/600mA). In general, we didn\'t suggest the customer replace the battery, we suggest you to charge the battery in direct sunlight up to 8h to ensure the battery get fully charged.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Qedertek Direct&nbsp;on September 22, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>when you check out the price of the batteries, you will probably just wanna get a new set of lights....also, looks like you are in the NW probably not enough sunlight to charge fully.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By BEACH BABY on September 21, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1UEYYDYW44BA9\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				Does the solar panel need direct sunlight to get powered?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span>Yes, it does.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Azuki-chan on April 20, 2016</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1V10KHQVH1YHT\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				Do they use rechargable by the sun bateries? if so, what kind aa or aaa?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:13.3333px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;font-family:HelveticaNeue, &quot;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span>Mine run on one AA NiCad rechargeable. I had some several years ago and I love them. I recently bought several more and the price is much cheaper now than when I bought the first few sets.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By John M. on March 28, 2017</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx1V10KHQVH1YHT\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1V10KHQVH1YHT-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>No batteries needed at all. They have a solar panel with a post to put in the ground. Charge in the sun for eight hours and they are good to go. Very easy to use. Nice light. They are great so far.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Jalapeño 023 on March 24, 2017</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>There are no batteries. The strand of lights have a small solar panel attached at one end that can be attached to a stake or simply hung facing the sun. Handsfree!</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on March 29, 2017</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div>\r\n						<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\"><br />\r\n</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>', 'Solar String Lights: 30 LED Crystal Ball String Lights, Warm White Christmaslights, Holiday Festival of Lights - Qedertek', 'warm white string light decoration,crystal ball christmaslights,holiday festival of lights,solar crystal ball lights', 'If you are looking for holiday festival of lights，don\'t miss this 30 LED Crystal Ball String Lights，Christmaslights，features 8 modes and waterproof, perfect for adding warm and charming atmosphere to holidays even your daily life.', 'https://www.amazon.com/dp/B01DPCKFRW/', '', '0', '0.00', 'http://images.qedertek.com/59352ef44c47f', '{\"59352ef46cbcd\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352ef46cbcd\",\"59352ef49053f\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352ef49053f\",\"59352ef4c730c\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352ef4c730c\",\"59352ef50306a\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59352ef50306a\"}', '0', '1', '0', '0.00', '1', '1491446104', '1496657653', '', '0');
