dy on. Switch the mode button to convert between these 8 kinds modes, no visual fatigue, no dull any more&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:700;\">Automatic Timer Function</span><br />\r\n&nbsp;The lights have been pre-programmed with timing sequence, auto cycle of 6 hours on and then 18 hours off everyday, no need of manual operation, super convenient.<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:700;\">Endless Application</span><br />\r\n&nbsp;Placement options have no limitation. those mini led lights will create a starry fairy scene for your home, garden, window, gazebo, deck railing, stairs, wedding, showcase, party, dance hall, stage and so on.&nbsp;<br />\r\nThere\'s no place it can\'t be applied to decorate, but only place you can\'t think of&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:700;\">Specifications:</span><br />\r\n&nbsp;Light Color: Warm White&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;Battery: 3 x D size&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;Cable length: Total length 15.7M/50ft, lead length: 30CM/0.98ft, lamp spacing: 7.7CM/0.25ft&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;LED Quantity: 200pcs, 200 LED at 7.7CM/0.25ft spacing&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:700;\">What\'s in the Box？</span><br />\r\n&nbsp;1 x Qedertek 200LED Battery Powered String Lights&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;1 x User Instruction\r\n											</p>\r\n										</div>\r\n									</div>\r\n								</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>', '<ul class=\"a-unordered-list a-vertical a-spacing-none\" style=\"color:#949494;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Ideal for Indoor and Outdoor Decor: The outdoor string lights illuminate during night, add warm and charming atmosphere to your garden, patio, lawn, porch, gate, yard, etc</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Battery Powered String Lights: 200 bright warm white LEDs lights on the 50ft light strand (0.98ft lead cable included), powered by 3 x D batteries (not included), high-brightness but not dazzling</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Timer Function: Auto ON/OFF for all lighting modes, 6 hours \"ON\" and 18 hours \"OFF\"</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Easy to Operate &amp; Install: Easy operation with only one switch, 8 lighting modes</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Waterproof: IP65 waterproof rate for the lights string, and IP44 for the battery box, which is suitable for indoor &amp; outdoor decorations</span> \r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', '<div id=\"question-Tx2YCXEHZ0R6PT6\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n			<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n			Specifically on the qedertek battery operated christmas string lights that use 3 d batteries, how many days do the batteries last with 6 hrs on?\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n			<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n			<span>They use (3) three D batteries and I can them about every 6 to 8 weeks</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Tawney Hale on November 19, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx2YCXEHZ0R6PT6\"> \r\n			<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx2YCXEHZ0R6PT6-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n				<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n					<span>I put the first batteries in and they last about 1 week. I tried with 3 other batteries and now these have lasted since the weekend after Thanksgiving. It is Jan 15 now and the lights are just starting to look less bright. So, I think 6-8 weeks is about right.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Raindrop on January 15, 2017</span> \r\n				</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx3GQ1SAPGKVI08\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Are they UL tested/approved?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>To be honest i don\'t know..We are using them for a tree outside and i know longer have the info from the lights..</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Michelle on December 1, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx3GQ1SAPGKVI08\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx3GQ1SAPGKVI08-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Yes. Plus you have the protection of Amazon no hassle returns</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By John T. on December 1, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Yes, I bought these lights last year and they still work wonderful, so I bought more for this year. I really like them.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Kimberly U. on December 2, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx17R9RDQC0BEPV\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				How does the timer work? There is a \"timer\" sticker but when I scroll through it does not light up.\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>The timer is one of the top two...I believe one is for 6 hrs and the other is for 13 hrs. Just press the one you want</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Tawney Hale on December 7, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx17R9RDQC0BEPV\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx17R9RDQC0BEPV-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Did you check if your batteries are good? Mine do not have a sticker, but a raised button to turn them on.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on December 6, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx19H30957L1AZQ\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Are these solar lights or battery lights?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>You can see the battery container sitting next to the lights, I think these use three d cell and have eight nodes. I stopped buying this brand because they started to raise the price on them so I went to a different brand. I have several sets of lights on our property, it looks nice.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Sharon from cal. on December 5, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx19H30957L1AZQ\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx19H30957L1AZQ-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>They are battery operated lights like the title description says. They take D size batteries.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By cdjones on December 5, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>They are battery operated</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By TONI MARIE WILCZEWSKI on December 5, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Battery</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Ben and Amanda on December 5, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1PRLC7QSC2JM\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				what is the measurements of the battery box please?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>We absolutely love ours. All of the neighbors comment on how great they look. We have been very satisfied!</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on January 8, 2017</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx1PRLC7QSC2JM\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1PRLC7QSC2JM-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>I don\'t have it with me, but I\'d guess 2 x 4 x 7ish inches. It\'s definitely too heavy to hang from a wall, but it\'s totally fine if the battery box can be on the floor or sit on some surface. Not a big deal for us.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Katria L on January 9, 2017</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>It\'s about 4.72*3.34*1.37 inches</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Qedertek Direct&nbsp;on January 10, 2017</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1PRLC7QSC2JM-2\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>approx. 3 x 8 inches</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Liftaholic on January 9, 2017</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>I\'d say approximately 2 inches wide by 4 inches long</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on January 8, 2017</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>It\'s big , It weighs to much, the wires pull right out of it as soon as the batteries were installed, I had to throw away</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on January 8, 2017</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx21NSQE6NFXGK1\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Can anyone provide the DC voltage of this item?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>It uses batteries</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Judy Van Nostrand on January 11, 2017</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx21NSQE6NFXGK1\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx21NSQE6NFXGK1-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>4.5</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Elizabeth K. on January 10, 2017</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>4.5 DC VOLTAGE</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By tony on January 13, 2017</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx25WFPRGQ1O65S\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Do they have to use timer or can you just manually turn off and on when you want them on?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>You don\'t have to use the timer. However if you use the timer and for example turn on the lights at 6 pm, they will turn off at midnight and then the following days they will repeat the cycle on at 6 and off at 12 until you turn the timer off.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Carolyn Farley on February 22, 2017</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx25WFPRGQ1O65S\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx25WFPRGQ1O65S-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>You can turn them on and off whenever you want I believe. I used the timer function.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Liftaholic on February 21, 2017</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>It auto sets a timer, but you can turn it off and on too.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Colleen LaRue on February 21, 2017</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx25WFPRGQ1O65S-2\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Manually turn on and off</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Lawrence Kirk on February 21, 2017</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Yes; however, if you leave them on I think they will automatically turn off after six hours.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Pam Elms Scott on February 21, 2017</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>You can set it on a timer or you can turn them on and off yourself. Love it.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By gio on February 22, 2017</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx2Q2YTYLCIHWBZ\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Water proof?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>Yes! Ours have been in the rain several times now and they are still going strong!</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on December 19, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx2Q2YTYLCIHWBZ\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx2Q2YTYLCIHWBZ-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>According to the description on amazon, yes. We have them strung outside in a tree, so I hope so!</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Allison Brown on December 19, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Yes</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on December 19, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx2RUWKVAHJJXMW\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Where is the timer function located on the box?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>there is no real timer. You turn it on at whatever time you like and it stays on for 6 hours, then shuts off for 18 hours and then comes back on. These just repeats. So on for 6 and off for 18. I was confused also when we received ours.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Steve D. on December 10, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx2RUWKVAHJJXMW\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx2RUWKVAHJJXMW-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Once you set how you want the lights to work the internal timer counts to 6 hours and shuts off. It will automatically come on after 18 hours.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Lorrie Rutter on December 10, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>On the top of the Battery box</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on December 10, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx2RUWKVAHJJXMW-2\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>The timer is based on 6 hours after you turn it on</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Wally on December 10, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>It isn\'t on box it has a six hour timer automatic.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Sharon Renee Gray on December 10, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx2TLROOHKWQQG8\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.3333px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div clas