r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px -100px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n				<span>I just put these on my wreath and they are great. Off for 18 and back on for 6 hours. Just set the FIRST time at the time you always want them to go on. Not sure how long batteries last but so far so good for 1 week with no signs of dimming out.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Leamarie H Amorosi on December 7, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"TxBC97H6ADD2M2\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-TxBC97H6ADD2M2-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>They automatically come back on to rather same setting.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Pamela Davidge on December 7, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>They\'re on a timer so they automatically turn back on the next day.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on December 7, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\">\r\n						<span>They go on automatically if you use the time feature. Each strand requires 3 C batteries so the box isn\'t exactly light. I use them on a wreath located on an outside bench so the battery box sits on the bench. Also they can be used outside, the