le=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				The product description says 33\' &amp; the specifications say 20\' Which is it?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span class=\"askExpanderContainer askExpanderExpanded\"><span class=\"askLongText\">The blue ones I ordered in October are 33\' in length. On the warm white I ordered in October they are also 33\'. When i tried to re-order recently (warm white) they were unavailable and did not know when they would be in stock, however they offer the 20\' with 120 leds, so I ordered a couple of them. Word of warning: Be careful when you start unwinding them, they tangle easily, but over all are very pretty and easier than fooling with a bunch of green cords with lights. I plan on decorating my tree with them. I will post a picture when done. Hope this helps.&nbsp;</span></span><br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By chubby58 on November 12, 2015</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1E4LN7JUO236V\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				What\'s the best way to attach/mount them to a wall? I\'d like to put them up where ceiling meets wall. Thx!\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>I just used tacks, but you might want to look into buying that picture hanging adhesive and cut them into thin strips. That\'s what I use to mount the solar panel to the window.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Frederick S. on February 23, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx1E4LN7JUO236V\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx1E4LN7JUO236V-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>My grand daughter draped them across her headboard, they look adorable, she\'s 8 years old and loves it</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By nancy mullen on February 23, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>You can really use anything as it is very lightweight and the \"string\" the lights are attached to is like wire, which is easily bendable. I have mine hung up with nails, and I looped the wire around each nail to hold it up. Hope this helps!</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Lisa de Felice on February 24, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx1F50P2GUGTGEJ\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Have the colors changed in the last 2 months? the first 4 strings i bought were warm rygb. the colors on the last string i got are intense and cold.\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>I have been using mine and still have the same colors since I brought it I think is been April since</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Alicia on May 16, 2016</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx23XGH4VLO2ATT\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Can you dim these lights?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>No you can\'t.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on March 2, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx23XGH4VLO2ATT\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx23XGH4VLO2ATT-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>No you cannot dim the lights....but they are a very soft lighting I have received many compliments on how pretty they are. Hope this helps.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on March 2, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>No. These are non dimmable</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Candy on March 2, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx23XGH4VLO2ATT-2\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>A dimmer is not supplied, so unless you have some means of dimming them yourself, I doubt it. You\'d need to talk with the manufacturer to see if they are even rated for that.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Alexandra Wigle on March 2, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>You can not dim the lights. They go everywhere, and do not get hot. Enjoy</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Cathy G. on March 2, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx296NGO4X38WD3\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Would these be ok to use as a bedroom decoration for a child?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>I would not use them in a child\'s room. They are very small lights and Ibwoukd be afraid my child would somehow get it into their mouth.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Diana Marks on January 27, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx296NGO4X38WD3\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx296NGO4X38WD3-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>I don\'t know why not, as long as they were plugged into an inaccessible outlet if the child is young. And also that they were securely attached to the wall or ceiling. If you think that your child would be pulling on the wires or lights then I would say that no type of string light would be a good idea.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By HunniB on January 27, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx2NIDBS5KXW6E4\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Do these lights flash?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>No, unless I missed something. I purchased these to use at Easter time and didn\'t even look to see if they flash. They are very bright and pretty.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Alynn Brodine on April 25, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx2NIDBS5KXW6E4\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx2NIDBS5KXW6E4-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>They don\'t flash or twinkle.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Sue on April 26, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>No they don\'t.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Amazon Customer on April 25, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx2NIDBS5KXW6E4-2\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Not as packaged. You would need the control adapter that some of the more expensive ones come with.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By P Lucci on April 25, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>No they do not but they are bright and beautiful</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Kindle Customer on April 25, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>No, they do not.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Lisa de Felice on April 25, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx2XEKAZXMKEVB5\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				My deck is 30 feet long on one side so how many should I buy just for that side? Is it a good product to use on a railing?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>At least 2 strands. I think it\'s ok to use on a railing. The strings are wire so it was not easy to work with</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By amk on June 20, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx2XEKAZXMKEVB5\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx2XEKAZXMKEVB5-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>for that length I would say about 10. this is just an estimate. the lights are small so for more color to stand out I would double the lights but that is my opinion.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Doodle on June 20, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span class=\"askExpanderContainer\"><span class=\"askShortText\">You could get by with purchasing 1 string of starry lights for one side because the lights are so very bright for their size. It is a spectacular effect for 2 or more to be together. That being said, I do not see a way to plug the lights into each other so you would need to have an outlet for each strand. I love the lights</span></span><br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By For What Its Worth on June 20, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>I would buy 2, because the lights will reflect better. I have them up on the tops of my deck and railing. They shimmer much better. Also I live the 3rd floor up, and if you live close to the street or sidewalk, it will look much better. A side note, buy a timer and set them to come on and off. Enjoy them I do.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By August Michael on June 20, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx2YUB51DX5ACX5\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Are these safe to use on a fresh Christmas tree?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>Yes, no problem</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Fernando avila on November 27, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx2YUB51DX5ACX5\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx2YUB51DX5ACX5-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Being low voltage and on a properly care-for tree I would consider them safe. It\'s just me, but I would not leave a cut tree unattended, alone in the home. However, I feel the more fragile wiring would lend better to an artificial tree.<br />\r\nMerry Christmas<br />\r\nStan</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By StanJon on November 29, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>yes I have used them they look ok. Honestly the larger ones look better. These worked better on my smaller artificial tree than the larger tree.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Doodle on November 28, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx30DZ3J62KR0J3\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				is the only way to turn them off and on is to unplug and plug to an outlet?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>Yes</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By amk on June 4, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx30DZ3J62KR0J3\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx30DZ3J62KR0J3-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span class=\"askExpanderContainer\">Janette, yes, as produced, the light string must be plugged/unlpugged from the electrical outlet. However, an inline rotary or rocker switch can be wired inline of the power line at a location between the plug and the light copper wiring. Available at most hardware stores, the switch is simple to install.<br />\r\nTake Care</span><br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By StanJon on June 4, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Yes</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By amk on June 4, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx30DZ3J62KR0J3-2\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Yes.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Sue on June 4, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Yes,easier to plug it into a power strip</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Roderick Olivares on June 4, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-Tx358452JN3UJRT\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Are the rainbow color lights pastel? (The picture shows a pastel rainbow hue but I\'ve been fooled before by improperly lit and misleading photographs)\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>They are a tad bit softer than Christmas tree lights but I wouldn\'t call them pastel,even so at these prices you can\'t go wrong</span><br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Roderick Olivares on May 1, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx358452JN3UJRT\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx358452JN3UJRT-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Yes I think they do look pastel but it also depends on the table or where they placed them because it does look like there\'s a scheene there so it may not be a complete black table</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By August Michael on May 1, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>They are pastel.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Misakit on May 1, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx358452JN3UJRT-2\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>My rainbow lights look quite neon to me, but they are still very pretty.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By rosesdreamsandstardust on May 1, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Yes they do appear to be on the pastel side. They really looked great.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Tracy Potter on April 30, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-TxB3N7GDXOBOKM\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Are they safe for outdoor use?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>I use my lights inside my deck on the ceiling. They are outside, but in a screened deck area.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Linda on July 19, 2016</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"TxB3N7GDXOBOKM\"> \r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-TxB3N7GDXOBOKM-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Yes, I put theme on my gate</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Frederick S. on July 18, 2016</span> \r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span> \r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>', '100 LED Starry Copper Rope Lights String| Multicolor Decor Copper Wire Lights - Qedertek', 'plug-in string lights,100 led Christmas lights,electric power Christmas lights,copper wire lights,Xmas decor lights', 'Electric powered 100 led flexible copper wire lights, high brightness, perfect fit for all Christmas, party & lighting decor needs', 'https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00YG5HIK0/', '', '0', '12.99', 'http://images.qedertek.com/5982a32140545', '{\"5982a322ce8bd\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/5982a322ce8bd\",\"5982a322f4151\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/5982a322f4151\",\"5982a323146a6\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/5982a323146a6\",\"5982a32328d56\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/5982a32328d56\",\"5982a3233d51c\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/5982a3233d51c\"}', '0', '0', '1', '0.00', '1', '1501733667', '1501738924', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `qe_product` VALUES ('91', '11', '28LED Solar Motion Wall Light Security Lamp, Waterproof', '<p>\r\n	<img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/S/aplus-seller-content-images-us-east-1/ATVPDKIKX0DER/A231TAZUOKNIOW/B072M6ZXTQ/4JMCRYL6RUel._UX970_TTW__.jpg\" title=\"Qedertek Solar Motion Sensor Lights\" alt=\"Qedertek Solar Motion Sensor Lights\" />\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:&quot;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;font-weight:700 !important;\"><strong>Qedertek Solar Motion Sensor Light</strong></span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#111111;font-family:&quot;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">With upgraded design, the 28LED solar motion sensor lights can illuminate a larger range with ideal brightness.</span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:&quot;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;font-weight:700 !important;\"><strong>Features</strong></span><br />\r\n<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:&quot;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;font-weight:700 !important;\">1.</span><span class=\"a-text-italic\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:&quot;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;font-style:italic !important;\">3-IN-1 working modes:</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#111111;font-family:&quot;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">a.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:&quot;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;font-weight:700 !important;\">Only Light Sensor Mode</span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-family:&quot;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">: auto-on and in a Steady status when its dark, and auto-off in a bright environment; &nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#111111;font-family:&quot;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">b.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:&quot;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;font-weight:700 !important;\">Light Sensor + Motion Sensor:</span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-family:&quot;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;auto-on&nbsp;in darkness in&nbsp;Power Saving mode(Dim Light),&nbsp;turn to&nbsp;High Brightness&nbsp;when people go through the induction area,&nbsp;then back to dim light 15s later when people leave.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#111111;font-family:&quot;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">c.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:&quot;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;font-weight:700 !important;\">Only Motion Sensor Mode</span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-family:&quot;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">:&nbsp;auto-on&nbsp;when problem go through the detection area in&nbsp;High Brightness&nbsp;Status, then&nbsp;auto-off&nbsp;15s later when people leave.</span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#111111;font-family:&quot;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">2.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:&quot;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;font-weight:700 !important;\">Solar Powered</span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-family:&quot;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">, environmental protection, no electricity costs, cost-effective.</span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#111111;font-family:&quot;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">3.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:&quot;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;font-weight:700 !important;\">Waterproof,</span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-family:&quot;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;can withstand any kind of weather. &nbsp;Widely used in for Home, Garden, Barn, Porch and so on, Easily operation, let the solar led motiona sensor lights bring you a bright and safe world.</span>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<div class=\"celwidget aplus-module 3p-module-c\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:&quot;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"aplus-3p-fixed-width\">\r\n			<h3 class=\"a-spacing-mini\" style=\"margin-left:0px;font-size:17px;\">\r\n				Motion Sensor Lights\r\n			</h3>\r\n			<div class=\"a-row\">\r\n				<div class=\"a-column a-span4 a-spacing-base\">\r\n					<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/S/aplus-seller-content-images-us-east-1/ATVPDKIKX0DER/A231TAZUOKNIOW/B072M6ZXTQ/YlV6nBE6Si24._UX300_TTW__.jpg\" />\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div class=\"a-column a-span8 a-spacing-base a-span-last\">\r\n					<p>\r\n						<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Detail for the Solar Motion Sensor Lights</span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n1.&nbsp;<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Solar Powered</span>, with high conversion, 17% conversion rate.<br />\r\n2. One Motion Sensor,&nbsp;<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">the detect angle is 150°</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">wider</span>&nbsp;than the same products from other sellers. The detecting distance can reach as far as 8M(26.24ft).<br />\r\n3.&nbsp;<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">28&nbsp;Super bright LED lights</span>, with 120lm for each one. Enough for illumination in daily life.<br />\r\n4. &nbsp;With the Li-ion Battery inside,&nbsp;<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">charge solar power automatically</span>.<br />\r\n5. With functional switch on the back of the lights,&nbsp;<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">3 working mode with power off function</span>, choose &nbsp;the one you like most!<br />\r\n6.<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">The detecting time can last 15s after the motion sensor ending.</span>\r\n					</p>\r\n				</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"celwidget aplus-module 3p-module-c\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:&quot;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"aplus-3p-fixed-width\">\r\n			<h3 class=\"a-spacing-mini\" style=\"margin-left:0px;font-size:17px;\">\r\n				Waterproof Solar LED Motion Sensor Lights\r\n			</h3>\r\n			<div class=\"a-row\">\r\n				<div class=\"a-column a-span4 a-spacing-base\">\r\n					<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/S/aplus-seller-content-images-us-east-1/ATVPDKIKX0DER/A231TAZUOKNIOW/B072M6ZXTQ/UzQjiYVySS2E._UX300_TTW__.jpg\" />\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div class=\"a-column a-span8 a-spacing-base a-span-last\">\r\n					<p>\r\n						<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\"><span class=\"a-text-italic\" style=\"font-style:italic !important;\">Waterproof</span>, so do not worry about the lights even its rainy or snowy outside.</span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Warm Tips:</span><br />\r\n1. Please install the lights with its solar panel can face the sun light directly;<br />\r\n2. If there is several days without sun lights, the lights working will be influenced, and need longer time to charge.<br />\r\n3. If the motion sensor lights do not work at the beginning, please check if the lights is ON status.\r\n					</p>\r\n				</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"celwidget aplus-module 3p-module-d\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:&quot;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"aplus-3p-fixed-width\">\r\n			<h3 class=\"a-spacing-mini\" style=\"margin-left:0px;font-size:17px;\">\r\n				Easy to Install and Operate\r\n			</h3>\r\n			<div class=\"a-row\">\r\n				<div class=\"a-column a-span4 a-spacing-base\">\r\n					<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/S/aplus-seller-content-images-us-east-1/ATVPDKIKX0DER/A231TAZUOKNIOW/B072M6ZXTQ/d14PLWwfSFu1._UX300_TTW__.jpg\" class=\"a-spacing-base\" />\