FFF;\">Specifications:</span><span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:&quot;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:&quot;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Solar panel: 0.55W, 17% efficiency&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:&quot;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Li-ion battery: 3.7V 1000mAh&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:&quot;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">LED: 16&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:&quot;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Lumens: 100lm&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:&quot;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">Solar charging time: 8 hours&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:700;color:#333333;font-family:&quot;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">What\'s in the box:</span><span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:&quot;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:&quot;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1 x Solar Wall Light&nbsp;</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#333333;font-family:&quot;font-size:small;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">1 x User Manual</span>', '<ul class=\"a-unordered-list a-vertical a-spacing-none\" style=\"color:#949494;font-family:&quot;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Perfect Outdoor Light: Light built-in 16 LED, 2 working modes, super bright, solid construction, waterproof design, easy installation, ideal to use in garden, patio, deck,driveway, stairway, sheds, walkway, outside walls etc.</span>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">3-In-1 Sensoring Light: PIR/Motion/Lighting Sensor technology, motion sensor triggers within10ft and at a 120 degree angle</span>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">2 Intelligent Modes Optional: Dim/Bright light mode. Dim light mode-light will auto on with dim light in darkness, when motion detected, light become strong, then stay on with dim light without motion. Bright light mode-at night, light auto no only when motion is activated, and when motion gone, it will last about 35-40 seconds, then turns off for energy saving</span>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Updated Battery: Built-in 3.7V 1000mAh Li-ion battery, absorb much more sunlight and high conversion rate, long running time</span>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span class=\"a-list-item\" style=\"color:#111111;\">Solar Powered: Operated by solar with large solar panel, ultra bright, energy saving and environment friendly</span>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', '<div id=\"question-Tx3RNYVR6V23HT0\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n			<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n			How much charge (daily) does this product need to work? Can it be used indoors, for example, where it will not get full sun? E.g. warehouse facility.\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n			<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n			<span>I was actually surprised how well it charged in the house. So well I had to turn it so the solar panel was not exposed. I am not sure how many hours of charge it received in this manner.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Alaria Sun on January 4, 2017</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"Tx3RNYVR6V23HT0\"> \r\n			<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-Tx3RNYVR6V23HT0-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n				<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n					<span class=\"askExpanderContainer askExpanderExpanded\"><span class=\"askLongText\">Until it quits snowing, I have the light with the solar cells facing outdoors in a window that gets occasional sun and when it does it generally works all night. If it is cloudy, the light quits working about 3 or 4am. If indoor lighting is bright enough to switch off the LEDs then the unit will charge a little but not enough to run all night. I\'m sure that when I get this unit mounted come spring, the light will work, sun or clouds, long enough into the evening to light the way for people to come and go.</span></span><br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By James D. Anderson on January 4, 2017</span> \r\n				</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n</span> \r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-TxCQP824KNKVY4\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span>\r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				What light temperature is the LED? Example: Warm 3000K or Cool 6000K\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span>\r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>Looks like daylight, bright white</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Henry A. Granger, Jr. on May 3, 2017</span><span class=\"askInlineAnswers\" id=\"TxCQP824KNKVY4\">\r\n				<div id=\"askInlineAnswersPage-TxCQP824KNKVY4-1\" class=\"a-section a-spacing-none\">\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>Its pretty bright abt 6k</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Mohan Ramnath on May 2, 2017</span>\r\n					</div>\r\n					<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-none a-spacing-top-small\">\r\n						<span>they are cool to the touch</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By BJ White on May 2, 2017</span>\r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n</span>\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-TxINXD5OX6SXHM\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span>\r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				does the built in battery needs changing?\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span>\r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>Just put the device on the sun for a day before swithing it.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By Ephim Shirman on November 16, 2016</span>\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"question-TxSS6Z6A2ONAAT\" class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-small\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Question:</span>\r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				Anyone know how to change the mode? Claims to have two user selectable modes, no switch.\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid a-spacing-base\" style=\"color:#111111;font-family:verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13px;background-color:#FFFFFF;\">\r\n		<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-inner\" style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 100px;\">\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-left\" style=\"margin-left:-100px;\">\r\n				<span class=\"a-text-bold\" style=\"font-weight:700 !important;\">Answer:</span>\r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"a-fixed-left-grid-col a-col-right\">\r\n				<span>Default mode is dim after dark, second mode is full bright when motion sensor is triggered. You can\'t switch modes.</span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span class=\"a-color-tertiary\" style=\"color:#767676 !important;\">By L A four20 on April 11, 2017</span>\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>', 'Motion Security Lights | 16 LED Outdoor Wall Lights- Qedertek', 'solar motion detector lights,motion detector lights,led motion lights,outdoor motion lights', 'Solar powered 16 LED motion detector lights, outdoor motion lights, ideas lighting and security to your garage, pathway driveway, stairway, sheds, walkway, outside walls etc.', 'https://www.amazon.com/dp/B01MFCLV7V/', '', '0', '0.00', 'http://images.qedertek.com/59896ebee3310', '{\"59896ebf1e452\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59896ebf1e452\",\"59896ebf39f4c\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59896ebf39f4c\",\"59896ebf58476\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59896ebf58476\",\"59896ebf66f4e\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59896ebf66f4e\",\"59896ebf77f65\":\"http:\\/\\/images.qedertek.com\\/59896ebf77f65\"}', '0', '0', '1', '0.00', '1', '1502179007', '1502179007', '', '0');
